review_blob: So far my favorite of the Belgiun style beers. Godd fruity flavor, more of a cherry taste but not overwhelming. Number one with me so far.
Very citrusy flavor. Very much like a strong pale aile. Creamy with a bit of yeast on the bottom.
You need to like a strong beer for this one. Great malty tatse with a slight bite. Some what of a fruity flavor. Liked it.
This was a good tasting beer. Was like an Octoberfest beer. Not too malty, medium dark. Serve in a frosty mug1
